<h1>Cacao Overnight Oats</h1>
<h2>Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
<li>1/3 cup rolled oats</li>
<li>2 teaspoons cacao powder</li>
<li>2 teaspoons chia seeds</li>
<li>4 teaspoons agave</li>
<li>6 tablespoons water</li>
</ul>
<h2>Ingredients (triple batch)</h2>
<ul>
<li>1 cup rolled oats</li>
<li>6 teaspoons cacao powder</li>
<li>6 teaspoons chia seeds</li>
<li>4 tablespoons agave</li>
<li>1 1/4 cup water</li>
</ul>
<h2>Instructions</h2>
<ol>
<li>Add all ingredients to a 1/2-pint mason jar (2-pint mason jar if doing a triple batch).</li>
<li>Close the lid.</li>
<li>Shake vigorously for five seconds.</li>
<li>Place in the fridge overnight.</li>
<li>Serve the next day (or up to a week later) with sliced banana, chopped strawberries, frozen blueberries, or any combination of fruits on hand.</li>
</ol>
